# 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 MapReduce End-to-End Data Flow Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A1[HDFS Input File\ninput.txt 128MB Split 1] --> M1
    A2[HDFS Input File\ninput.txt 128MB Split 2] --> M2
    A3[HDFS Input File\ninput.txt 128MB Split 3] --> M3

    M1[Mapper Node 1\nTokenize + Filter\nhadoop, hadoop, bigdata] -->|Partition by Key| C1[Combiner Node 1\nLocal Aggregation\nhadoop:2, bigdata:1]
    M2[Mapper Node 2\nTokenize + Filter\nmapreduce, hadoop, yarn] -->|Partition by Key| C2[Combiner Node 2\nLocal Aggregation\nmapreduce:1, hadoop:1, yarn:1]
    M3[Mapper Node 3\nTokenize + Filter\nhdfs, hadoop, mapreduce] -->|Partition by Key| C3[Combiner Node 3\nLocal Aggregation\nhdfs:1, hadoop:1, mapreduce:1]

    C1 -->|Shuffle and Sort| R1[Reducer Node 1\nFinal Aggregation\nhadoop:5]
    C2 -->|Shuffle and Sort| R2[Reducer Node 2\nFinal Aggregation\nbigdata:3, yarn:2]
    C3 -->|Shuffle and Sort| R3[Reducer Node 3\nFinal Aggregation\nmapreduce:3, hdfs:2]

    R1 --> O1[HDFS Output\npart-r-00000\nhadoop 5]
    R2 --> O2[HDFS Output\npart-r-00001\nbigdata 3\nyarn 2]
    R3 --> O3[HDFS Output\npart-r-00002\nmapreduce 3\nhdfs 2]
```

