> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning — Common Pitfalls:**
> 1. **Forgetting `toLowerCase()`**: Students often forget case normalization, leading to "Hadoop" and "hadoop" being counted as different words. **[-2 marks]**
> 2. **Punctuation not stripped**: Tokens like "hadoop," (with comma) fail to match "hadoop" in the keyword set. Use `replaceAll("[^a-zA-Z0-9]", "")`. **[-1 mark]**
> 3. **Not setting `setJarByClass()`**: The Driver class must call `job.setJarByClass()` so YARN can distribute the JAR to worker nodes. Forgetting this causes runtime errors. **[-2 marks]**
> 4. **Confusing `setMapOutputKeyClass` vs `setOutputKeyClass`**: The first is for Mapper→Reducer intermediate output; the second is for the final output. If Mapper and Reducer use the same types, both must be set. **[-1 mark]**
> 5. **Not handling the `setup()` method initialization**: Forgetting to initialize the keyword set in `setup()` leads to `NullPointerException`. **[-1 mark]**
> 6. **Output directory already exists**: Hadoop refuses to overwrite an existing output directory. Always delete the output directory before re-running. **[-1 mark]**

