# Section 3: Step-by-Step Derivations & Analytical Matrix

## 3.1 Mathematical Derivation of the Average Word Length Formula

The computation is straightforward but we will derive it formally to satisfy the KTU Board's rigor standards.

### 3.1.1 Single-Node Sequential Derivation

Given an input text corpus $T$ consisting of $M$ words $\mathcal{W} = \{w_1, w_2, \ldots, w_M\}$:

**Step 1:** Define the *first-character extraction function*:

$$f(w) = \begin{cases} \text{uppercase}(w[0]) & \text{if } w \text{ is non-empty} \\ \text{undefined} & \text{otherwise} \end{cases}$$

**Step 2:** Define the *word length function*:

$$\ell(w) = \vert w \vert \quad \text{(number of characters in } w\text{)}$$

**Step 3:** For each character $c \in \{A, \ldots, Z\}$, define the **subset of words beginning with $c$**:

$$\mathcal{W}_c = \{ w \in \mathcal{W} \;:\; f(w) = c \}$$

**Step 4:** The cardinality of this subset is:

$$N_c = \vert \mathcal{W}_c \vert = \sum_{w \in \mathcal{W}} \mathbb{1}[f(w) = c]$$

where $\mathbb{1}[\cdot]$ is the indicator function (returns 1 if true, 0 if false).

**Step 5:** The total length of all words beginning with $c$ is:

$$S_c = \sum_{w \in \mathcal{W}_c} \ell(w) = \sum_{w \in \mathcal{W}} \ell(w) \cdot \mathbb{1}[f(w) = c]$$

**Step 6:** Therefore, the **average word length for character $c$** is:

$$\mu_c = \frac{S_c}{N_c} = \frac{\sum_{w \in \mathcal{W}} \ell(w) \cdot \mathbb{1}[f(w) = c]}{\sum_{w \in \mathcal{W}} \mathbb{1}[f(w) = c]}$$

This is the **standard arithmetic mean** applied to the sub-population $\mathcal{W}_c$.

### 3.1.2 Worked Numerical Example

Consider the input text: `"Hadoop is great. Hello world! Are you there?"`

| Word | First Char | Length |
|---|---|---|
| Hadoop | H | 6 |
| is | I | 2 |
| great | G | 5 |
| Hello | H | 5 |
| world | W | 5 |
| Are | A | 3 |
| you | Y | 3 |
| there | T | 5 |

**Grouping and computing the average:**

$$
\begin{aligned}
\mu_A &= \frac{\ell(\text{Are})}{1} = \frac{3}{1} = 3.0 \\[4pt]
\mu_G &= \frac{\ell(\text{great})}{1} = \frac{5}{1} = 5.0 \\[4pt]
\mu_H &= \frac{\ell(\text{Hadoop}) + \ell(\text{Hello})}{2} = \frac{6 + 5}{2} = 5.5 \\[4pt]
\mu_I &= \frac{\ell(\text{is})}{1} = \frac{2}{1} = 2.0 \\[4pt]
\mu_T &= \frac{\ell(\text{there})}{1} = \frac{5}{1} = 5.0 \\[4pt]
\mu_W &= \frac{\ell(\text{world})}{1} = \frac{5}{1} = 5.0 \\[4pt]
\mu_Y &= \frac{\ell(\text{you})}{1} = \frac{3}{1} = 3.0
\end{aligned}
$$

> [!NOTE]
> **Expected Final Output (from the program):**
>
> ```text
> A    3.0
> G    5.0
> H    5.5
> I    2.0
