#### Model Solution for Q (a) — 7 Marks

**Step-by-step code structure:**

**Step 1: Mapper Class** (2 marks for correct key/value types and emission logic)

```java
public class AvgLenMapper extends Mapper<LongWritable, Text, Text, IntWritable> {
    private final Text outKey = new Text();
    private final IntWritable outVal = new IntWritable();

    public void map(LongWritable key, Text value, Context ctx)
            throws IOException, InterruptedException {
        StringTokenizer itr = new StringTokenizer(value.toString());
        while (itr.hasMoreTokens()) {
            String word = itr.nextToken().replaceAll("[^a-zA-Z]", "");
            if (word.isEmpty()) continue;
            outKey.set(String.valueOf(Character.toUpperCase(word.charAt(0))));
            outVal.set(word.length());
            ctx.write(outKey, outVal);
        }
    }
}
```

**Step 2: Reducer Class** (3 marks for the aggregation logic and average computation)

```java
public class AvgLenReducer extends Reducer<Text, IntWritable, Text, Text> {
    public void reduce(Text key, Iterable<IntWritable> values, Context ctx)
            throws IOException, InterruptedException {
        long sum = 0, count = 0;
        for (IntWritable v : values) { sum += v.get(); count++; }
        double avg = (count == 0) ? 0.0 : (double) sum / count;
        ctx.write(key, new Text("Avg: " + String.format("%.2f", avg)
                                + " | Count: " + count));
    }
}
```

**Step 3: Driver Class** (2 marks for Job configuration)

```java
