## 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **High-Density Revision Checklist – Memorize Before Exam:**

- [x] The **Mapper** emits `(firstChar, wordLength)`; the **Reducer** aggregates and averages.
- [x] Always use `long` (or `double`) for accumulators, **never `int`**, to avoid overflow on large inputs.
- [x] **Iterate the `Iterable` only once** in the Reducer — Hadoop reuses the same value object.
- [x] Set **both** `setMapOutputKeyClass` / `setMapOutputValueClass` (intermediate) and `setOutputKeyClass` / `setOutputValueClass` (final).
- [x] Use `replaceAll("[^a-zA-Z]", "")` to strip punctuation; otherwise `"Hello,"` ≠ `"Hello"`.
- [x] Convert the first character to **uppercase** to make the analysis case-insensitive.
- [x] Guard against `count == 0` to prevent `ArithmeticException` (defensive coding).
- [x] The `Combiner` is **optional** but reduces network traffic; it is *not* a substitute for the Reducer.
- [x] The `Partitioner` decides which Reducer gets which key (default: `HashPartitioner`).
- [x] Setting `numReduceTasks(0)` **skips the Reduce phase entirely** — output is just raw map emissions.
- [x] The default input format is `TextInputFormat` (line-by-line); default output format is `TextOutputFormat`.
- [x] Average formula: $\mu_c = \dfrac{\sum_{i=1}^{N_c} L_i}{N_c}$ — write this on your answer sheet if asked.
- [x] Compilation command: `javac -classpath $(hadoop classpath) -d classes *.java`.
- [x] Execution command: `hadoop jar <jarfile> <DriverClass> <input> <output>`.
- [x] View output: `hadoop fs -cat /path/to/output/part-r-00000`.
- [x] HDFS block size = **128 MB**; replication factor = **3** (Hadoop 3.x defaults).

